<p>This project is a cloud implementation of fast-neural-style in PyTorch. A React app was deployed in Heroku that can funcitons image style transformation via designed AWS cloud architecture and several Rest APIs. The application can be found at <a href="https://fast-transfer-style-ap.herokuapp.com/">here</a>.</p>

<h1 style="text-align: center;">EECS545-Implementation of XGBoost</h1>

<p>This project will focus on the implementation of the ensemble learning algorithm XGBoost.Based on the implementation, we will try to explore the reason behind the model decision from the feature perspective. As shown in figure ~\ref{fig:1}, we will also implement three build-in methods of XGBoost i.e. Gain, Weight, Cover and apply a plug-in method Tree SHAP[2]. Based on the implemented XGBoost, we apply those methods to selected datasets for calculating feature importance. With those values, we can explore the model interpretability also we will compare the effect of three methods by feature selection. In the end, we will analyze the experiment data and have some visualization to present our findings and conclusions.</p>
